# Moon Animation Project

This project demonstrates a simple moon animation using HTML and CSS. The moon pulsates and moves horizontally, creating a glowing effect.

## Table of Contents

- [Demo](#demo)
- [Project Structure](#project-structure)
- [Getting Started](#getting-started)
- [Usage](#usage)

## Demo

You can view a live demo of the project [here](#).

## Project Structure

```
.
├── index.html
└── README.md
```

- **index.html**: Contains the HTML structure and embedded CSS for the moon animation.
- **README.md**: This file, which provides an overview of the project.

## Getting Started

To get a local copy up and running, follow these steps:

### Prerequisites

All you need to run this project is a web browser.

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:

   ```sh
   git clone https://github.com/umeshyadav7988/moon-animation.git
   ```

2. Navigate to the project directory:

   ```sh
   cd moon-animation
   ```

3. Open the `index.html` file in your web browser to view the animation.

## Usage

- Open `index.html` in a web browser.
- The moon animation should start automatically.

### HTML Structure

The HTML file includes the following main sections:

- `<!DOCTYPE html>`: Defines the document type and version of HTML.
- `<head>`: Contains metadata and the title of the document.
- `<body>`: Contains the main content of the page, including the animated moon.

### CSS Styling

The CSS is embedded within the HTML file. It includes styling for the moon and the keyframe animation that creates the pulsating and moving effect.
